title: FK Proleter Novi Sad
text:
FK Proleter Novi Sad () is a professional <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club based in <a href="Novi%20Sad">Novi Sad</a>, <a href="Serbia">Serbia</a>. They compete in the <a href="Serbian%20SuperLiga">Serbian SuperLiga</a>, the top tier of the <a href="Serbian%20football%20league%20system">national league system</a>.
History.
Founded in 1951, the club won the <a href="Serbian%20League%20Vojvodina">Serbian League Vojvodina</a> in the <a href="2008%E2%80%9309%20Serbian%20League%20Vojvodina">2008–09 season</a> and took promotion to the <a href="Serbian%20First%20League">Serbian First League</a>. They spent the following nine years in the second tier of Serbian football, before winning the title and earning promotion to the <a href="Serbian%20SuperLiga">Serbian SuperLiga</a> for the first time in their history. During this period, the club also reached the <a href="Serbian%20Cup">Serbian Cup</a> round of 16 on five occasions. They would finish in eight place in their <a href="2018%E2%80%9319%20Serbian%20SuperLiga">debut appearance</a> in the top flight.
